PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1771959890
OL,3,C'No one beyond scrutiny': Parliament
OL,4,Cto release of documents on Andrew's
OL,5,Crole
OL,7,FSpeaking the House of Commons, Sir
OL,8,FChris Bryant said that the government
OL,9,Fwill "comply with the terms" of the
OL,10,Fmotion "in full".
OL,12,F"The government will of course comply
OL,13,Fwith the terms of the Humble Address
OL,14,Fin full. As I say, we support the
OL,15,Fmotion."
OL,17,FHe added that he did have "one caveat"
OL,18,F- the the government will not release
OL,19,Fanything that jeopardises the police
OL,20,Finvestigation.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1771959890
OL,3,C'No one beyond scrutiny': Parliament
OL,4,Cto release of documents on Andrew's
OL,5,Crole
OL,7,F"As the House will know, there is a
OL,8,Flive police investigation into the
OL,9,Fformer Duke of York after his arrest
OL,10,Fon suspicion of misconduct in public
OL,11,Foffice," he told MPs.
OL,13,F"As the police have rightly said, it
OL,14,Fis absolutely crucial that the
OL,15,Fintegrity of their investigation is
OL,16,Fprotected. And now these proceedings
OL,17,Fare underway, it will be wrong of me
OL,18,Fto say anything that might prejudice
OL,19,Fthem."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1771959890
OL,3,C'No one beyond scrutiny': Parliament
OL,4,Cto release of documents on Andrew's
OL,5,Crole
OL,7,F"Nor will the government be able to
OL,8,Fput into the public domain anything
OL,9,Fthat is required by the police for
OL,10,Fthem to conduct their inquiries unless
OL,11,Fand until the police are satisfied."
OL,13,FThey government has not yet set a
OL,14,Ftimeline but Bryant said they will
OL,15,Frelease the documents "as soon as they
OL,16,Fpossibly can".
OL,18,FIt means that the government will now
OL,19,Fhave to publish all papers relating to
OL,20,FAndrew's appointment, including any
OL,21,Fvetting and correspondence.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
